The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, May 03, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE FILM				 																																	(Nandan,  2 pm and 5.30 pm) Tapan Sinhas collection of short films  based on great stories written by great authors on the suffering  and neglect of womenfolk in different decades of the 20th  Century. Catch Shabana Azmi as Kadambini (above), Jaya Bachchan  as Abhagi, Nandita Das as Charu, Deepa Sahi as Champia and  Sulbha Deshpande as Hemlata  THE CD				 																																	(R.D.  Burman) A non-stop album containing some of Panchams fastest  tracks, which have been digitally re-mastered and mixed but  remain true to the original. From Piya tu ab to aaja,  Dum maro dum to Lekar hum diwana dil and Hum  dono do premi, the album is a delight. Check out the re-mastered  Dhanno ki aankhon mein and Chhodo sanam. Dont  miss Rafis Chura liya and Panchams Maria wail  from Gurudev.Timeless  THE FUNCTION				 																																	(May  9, 5.30 pm) Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture at Regent Park  will host a special programme at its auditorium. Participants  include Shaoli Mitra (above), Swagatalakshmi Dasgupta, Srikanta  Acharya and Pramita Mallick  THE BOOK				 																																	(Bob  McKerrow) After four years of fighting anarchy and destruction  in Kabul, a traffic policeman appeared in early 1995 at a  roundabout in the city, the first sign of civilian infrastructure,  bringing a ray of hope 

